---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Mirrored from '../components/Mirrored.astro';
import * as SampleReport from '../mirrored/sample-report.md';
import exampleYaml from '../mirrored/estate.example.yaml?raw';
import { PIN, REPO_URL } from '../config';
---
<Base
  title="A sample Executor File"
  description="What an Executor File actually looks like: the example register, the triage report the tool renders from it, and the printed page. All generated from the repository at build time."
>
  <div class="wrap prose">
    <section class="section">
      <h1>A sample Executor File</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Before downloading anything, see the real artefacts. Everything on this
        page is generated from the project's example register, with dummy data,
        at build time.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>The register</h2>
      <p>
        Plain YAML, readable in any editor. Notice what is absent: no passwords,
        no full account numbers. Entries point at where things are and say what
        you want done.
      </p>
      <Mirrored file="examples/estate.example.yaml" label="The example register, dummy data throughout">
        <pre tabindex="0"><code>{exampleYaml}</code></pre>
      </Mirrored>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>The triage report</h2>
      <p>
        After decrypting, the executor can render the register into a sorted,
        printable report: urgent things first, recurring charges by burn rate.
        Helpful, never required. This one was produced by running the tool's own{' '}
        <code>render.sh</code> on the example register during the site build.
      </p>
      <Mirrored file="scripts/render.sh" label="Report generated at build time by the tool's render script">
        <SampleReport.Content />
      </Mirrored>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>The printed page</h2>
      <p>
        The third artefact is the two-page Executor Instructions, stored with
        the will. The live copy is at <a href="/recover">/recover</a>, exactly
        as it prints; the template it is filled from is{' '}
        <a href={`${REPO_URL}/blob/${PIN.ref}/templates/EXECUTOR-INSTRUCTIONS.md`}>in the repository</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        Ready to make your own? <a href="/get-started">Get started</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Base>

<style is:global>
  .mirrored-body pre { max-height: 34rem; overflow: auto; }
</style>
